ğŸš€ Agentic RAG Chatbot â€” with Intelligent Meeting Scheduler

An advanced Agentic RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) chatbot that integrates:

Multi-agent reasoning (Router, Retriever, Grader)

FAISS vector retrieval over user resume & projects

LLM-driven decision routing (Groq API)

Automatic meeting scheduling via email trigger

This system not only answers context-aware questions using vector embeddings but also takes action â€” like scheduling meetings automatically when requested.

ğŸ§© Architecture Overview
ğŸ§  Agents Involved
Agent	Role	Description
Router Agent (LLM-A)	Route Decider	Determines whether the query should use resume, project, or meeting data.
Retriever Agent (LLM-A + FAISS)	Knowledge Fetcher	Retrieves the most relevant information from the embedded FAISS stores.
Grader Agent (LLM-B)	Evaluator	Evaluates if the generated answer fully satisfies the user query.
Meeting Node (Action Agent)	Executor	If the user requests a meeting, triggers an automated email notification.
