âš™ï¸ Installation & Setup
1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/Agentic-RAG-Chatbot.git
cd Agentic-RAG-Chatbot

2ï¸âƒ£ Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate   # On Windows
# or
source venv/bin/activate  # On macOS/Linux

3ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4ï¸âƒ£ Set up your .env file

Create a .env in the root directory with the following variables:

# --- LLM API Keys ---
GROQ_API_KEY_1=your_groq_key_1
GROQ_API_KEY_2=your_groq_key_2
GROQ_API_KEY_3=your_groq_key_3

# --- Email Credentials (App Password Required for Gmail) ---
EMAIL_USER=yourbot@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your_app_password

# --- Default Fallback Email (if user_data.json missing email) ---
DEFAULT_USER_EMAIL=test@example.com


ğŸ“§ Note: For Gmail, generate an App Password from
ğŸ‘‰ Google App Passwords

ğŸ§  How It Works
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Routing

The Router Agent (LLM-A) classifies your query as:

resume

project

both

meeting

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Retrieval (FAISS)

If not a meeting, it retrieves the most relevant embeddings from FAISS:

resume_index (personal background)

projects_index (GitHub/tech projects)

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: LLM Response Generation

Combines retrieved context with raw user JSON (user_data.json)
and generates a context-grounded answer using the Groq-hosted model.

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Meeting Trigger

If query or LLM output includes scheduling intent,
meeting_scheduler_node() sends a confirmation email automatically.

ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Grading (Optional)

The Grader Agent validates if the response is relevant and factual.
If failed, the system retries automatically with improved prompts.

ğŸ§© Key Code Snippets
ğŸ” Meeting Detection and Early Exit
if source == "meeting":
    meeting_scheduler_node("schedule a meeting")
    return "âœ… Meeting scheduled! Email notification sent."

ğŸ“§ Email Sending Logic
def send_meeting_email(to_email, subject, body):
    with smtplib.SMTP_SSL("smtp.gmail.com", 465) as server:
        server.login(os.getenv("EMAIL_USER"), os.getenv("EMAIL_PASS"))
        server.sendmail(os.getenv("EMAIL_USER"), to_email, body)

ğŸ§  Router Agent Example
prompt = """
You are a routing AI that decides which knowledge base or action to use.

Available routes:
1. resume
2. project
3. meeting
4. both
"""

